        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         ok i just have to jump in again...this is going to lower regen NOT stop it completely.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Zerging. Anti-regen a mob and bind everyone nearby. Zerg it and die. Since the mob's regenning at a very low speed, you can then buff up and zerg again, over and over, till the mob is dead. No skill required, really.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>boss mobs (whom this spell are intended to be used on) regen like MAD when they don't have agro (with the exception of IV).  most bosses go from 20% to full HP in a matter of just a minute or two...zerging would never work.</P><P>as for using this spell in regular exp; someone else commented on giving it a high mana cost, so the only time that would be used is if someone was trying to take down a tough named or something.  but keep in mind even regular mobs have mad regen when not agro'd...so while you *might* be able to kill it, it would probably take a LONG ass time.  plus the suggested levels by us have been 54+.  so imagine the type of mob you would be trying this with at that level...and that 54 one is going to be low...the lvl 59/60 one would only be 10 or 20%.</P><P>personally, i think this spell is a great idea.  i think there should be two versions...a lower mana cost one that only drops regen by like 5% or 10%(meant more for exp groups...have it cost around 150 or so like slows do); and a higher level one that has a high mana cost and a higher regen reduction...say around 15-20%.  i don't think it should be limited to 32K+ mobs, because that just hurts the guilds that are just getting capable of doing those 32k mobs.</P><P>as i said with DoT stacking...this spell will really only make it easier to do things that you are capable of.  what i mean is this...i'll use vindi as an example like i always do:  Your guild has been trying to kill vindi and keep getting close but can't quite get it, with this spell you should now be able to get him that little bit you have been missing.  however, if your guild couldn't even get vindi below 60% before, this spell isn't going to enable you to beat him now.</P><P>as for the, but this will only have one necro wanted on a raid...shaman are in the same boat; you only need 1 there to slow.  but most guilds will want a few back ups, so figure atleast 2 necro's on a raid...and figure a guild will want a few extra necro's in case those 2 aren't on.  personally, i see it as a way for necro's that previously couldn't get guilds to perhaps have a better chance.</P><P>this spell won't trivialize things anymore then slow does...and nothing comes close to touching what the CH cycle has done to the game.</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
