         Ok i got back from lunch early and decided to spend the rest of my lunch time typing up and sending the idea to VI...if you don't like the way i put it, well then submit it in your own way; sending in more then one doesn't hurt.  Well anyways, here it is...</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Recently on your...umm...favorite classes website (necro boards...i'm sure you guessed that but figured i'd tell you just in case) a spell idea was proposed.  we have kicked around the idea and argued a bit amongst ourselves to try and balance the spell.  Well I feel it is balanced so I've decided to submit it in.</P><P><BR>So without further adue....</P><P>The spell is a regen reducing spell, specifically meant for boss mob type encounters.  Two spells were originally suggested one being at around lvl 54 or 55 and doing about a 5-10% regen reduction; and another at lvl 59 or 60 and doing in the 10 to 20% range (the amount of reduction while keeping the spell balanced has been the main argument really).</P><P>The first one should have a lower mana cost (around 150-200ish), high agro(slow type agro), and short duration (about a minute).  That one would serve better in groups then raids but still be useful on raids (just due to how often it would need to be recasted and high agro, chances of the necro dying are high).  The second should have a high mana cost (around 400-600), high agro, and last for several minutes at least (personally, i think it should last about the same amount of time that slow does).</P><P>Now some issues are how might this effect the end game?  The answer is really not much...if a guild is capable of doing a mob, this will just make it a bit easier/safer, if a guild is almost able to kill a mob (can get it to around 20%) this might be just the edge they need to finally beat it, but if a guild isn't able to get the mob below even 50% this spell will really have no effect.</P><P>I'll use a quick example with Vindi...lets say Guild A is able to take vindi down easy; 30 people and about a 7 or 8 minute fight.  With this spell they should do it now in about 5-6 minutes. </P><P>Now Guild B is close to killing vindi with around 50-60 people, but they always seem to fail around 20-30%.  With this spell they *may* now be able to finally kill vindi, but it isn't a definite still.</P><P>Now Guild C tried vindi a few times with around 50-60 people, but could only get him to around 80%; with this spell, they might be able to get him down to 60%...but the issue is that until they gear up their MT a bit more so he can handle vindi's output, they aren't going to get him very far.<BR>--</P><P>Personally, I think that is a good example about how the spell might effect the higher end gaming.  Another issue that came up on the necro boards is could this spell be used to zerg?  the example someone gave was that you cast this and all charge in and die...then rebuff and keep doing it; but with the insane regen that boss mobs have that isn't even an issue...a 20% reduction in regen rate means they will simply be full HP in 3 minutes rather then 2.</P><P>And the other question is; what can necro's do with this solo?  Someone said that we could regen slow, DoT, FD...wait for DoTs to wear off, get back up and reapply.  The amount of time this would take to kill a regular exp mob would be about twice as long as it would normally take and the necro would only be doing one instead of the 2-4 we normally do, so in that instance it would be slower.  The other issue is what if we try that on a named or some such that normally takes a group?  Well any 55+ mob that we couldn't do before is most likely a summoning mob.  If you try this method then as soon as the DoTs wear off and you get back up to refresh, you are going to get summoned...and seriously, if the necro in question is uber enough to channel their DoTs and FD through a 55+ named melee; well personally i don't think a necro could unless they have about 3k unbuffed HP and full raid buffs and even then i don't think one could (and this makes up about 1% of the necro population).</P><P>---</P><P>Well, I guess that is all.  To quickly sum it up again...</P><P>Level: 54/55<BR>Spell Name: Unknown<BR>Effect: Slow mobs regen by 5% (lvl of spell) to 10% (lvl 60)<BR>Mana: 150/200<BR>Agro: High<BR>Resist check: Magic (have it add disease counters like slow so it can't be dispelled)<BR>Cast time: 5 seconds<BR>Recast time: 2 seconds</P><P>Level: 59/60<BR>Spell Name: Unknown<BR>Effect: Regen reduction by 15-20%<BR>Mana: 400/600<BR>Agro: High<BR>Resist Check: Magic (but have it add disease counters like slow so it can't be dispelled)<BR>Cast Time: 4 seconds<BR>Recast TIme: 2 seconds</P><P>Well there you have our proposed idea, if you think the amount of reduction is to high please adjust accordingly.</P><P>Also, if you want we have a discussion on this spell going on at...<BR>&lt;a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=6687"&gt;<a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=6687&lt;/a&gt;" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/forums/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=6687&lt;/a&gt;</a></P><P>please feel free to drop by and read over what we said...or better yet; give us some direct feed back on it.</P><P>Sincerly,</P><P>Daniel Knecht<BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu</P><P>P.S. Maelie of Innoruk is the one who originally posted the idea (though it has been ripped apart since then but still...) so any credit due should go to him/her.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
