			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=782')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=55237&amp;TOPIC_ID=6687&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=raiding%2Dnecros&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Three points abilister:</P><P>1. How fast do high-end mobs regen? Anyone have any HARD numbers on this? It's been my impression that certain mobs regen at amazing speeds even while in battle (Cazel), while others regen for jack even outside of combat (Velketor before he was buffed to prevent zerging, if I recall).  It sounds that this spell would be totally worthless in groups, because mobs you'll be fighting in groups regen at such a slow rate in combat and the fight will be over so soon that a 5-10% reduction every 6 seconds on the mob's regen means nothing.</P><P>Example: Let's assume your average 6k hp mob.  A typical fight with a mob like that lasts 1 minute.  10 ticks to one minute.  In order for this spell to be worth its casting cost (200 mana) it has to do around 500 damage, agreed? 500/10=50 regen stopped per tick.  If 50 regen was 10% of the mob's regen, then the mob would have to be regenning at 500/tick (or 5k per minute, which means Funeral Pyre AND Pyrocuror AND Epic stacked would not even overcome its regen!)  That's absurd.  If it was regenning at that speed our DoTs would do jack against it, and froglok dar knights would own most early 50's groups.</P><P>2. In truth, all the second spell would do is to be an uber DoT that only works on high-end fights.  I'm assuming that was the intended purpose, an uber DoT on high-end fights, in which case why not just make an uber DoT on high-end fights instead of asking for this? It seems to me this would be difficult to implement, seeing how there is no single damage-based spell in the game that works off of percentages.  Slow does, sure, but for all we know slow and haste could be on a totally different scale than most spells.</P><P>3. The only way this could help necros get guilds is if it made a HUGE difference in most fights AND could be maintained, due to its mana cost, by only the full effort of one necro (otherwise you'd just have the local uber necro casting it once and then DoTing as usual).  </P><P>Sure, this *would* be nice to have in theory, but without any hard numbers to back it up there is no telling what imbalance this may bring to the game.  Anyone know how fast the Arch Lich regens during combat, for instance? 1k/tick? 2k/tick? 3k/tick? As far as I know player regen isn't based on percentages (it's a flat number), so is there any reason why a mob's would be other than it seems like it? You need hard numbers to back up this spell, and that's something I haven't seen in this post at all.</P><P></P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
