         just because something is a flat number doesn't mean a % can't be taken out of it.  it isn't hard to code.  and you even stated that haste/slow works off %'s.  </P><P>for the most part this spell is pretty useless in groups, but there are occasions and places where it would have use.  there are a number of places that one group can hunt and have several minute fights...don't know about you but sometimes when a few guildies are bored and we are waiting for CT to pop a few of us will go into fear and screw around.  with only a few people fights can last for a good while.  the regen slower may not do a massive amount, but it will help.</P><P>as for why not just giving us another DoT...well you already stated that mobs regen at different rates...if you take into consideration how much HP this stop from being regen'd as *damage* then this spell would do more damage then most DoTs.</P><P>but as i said, this only makes fight easier...if your guild can't do AL without this spell, you aren't going to do him with this spell.  but i can garuntee if this spell goes live then every mob will be debuffed, shaman slowed, and then necro slowed.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
